And even if you can get access to them, a lot

00:13:18.480 --> 00:13:22.640
of times those application processes are lengthy and complicated and ask a

00:13:22.640 --> 00:13:26.230
lot of questions that an app of your scale doesn't really

00:13:26.330 --> 00:13:27.100
have an answer to.

00:13:27.100 --> 00:13:32.220
And platforms are reinventing these basic functionalities then instead of

00:13:32.220 --> 00:13:34.100
they can either use this third-party vendor or they can

00:13:34.100 --> 00:13:35.230
build it themselves.

00:13:35.230 --> 00:13:36.980
And that's a waste of efforts.

00:13:36.980 --> 00:13:41.420
It also takes away, it means that your app can't

00:13:41.420 --> 00:13:43.740
, or your app and your team can't focus on the

00:13:43.740 --> 00:13:47.080
harms that are specific to your community if you're focusing all

00:13:47.080 --> 00:13:49.270
of your time on building the same thing over and over again

00:13:49.270 --> 00:13:49.500
.

00:13:49.500 --> 00:13:51.980
We're also seeing that generative AI and LLMs

00:13:51.980 --> 00:13:55.260
are accelerating the production of and the spread of harms.

00:13:55.260 --> 00:14:00.690
So there's more and more things that are happening that need

00:14:00.690 --> 00:14:01.900
to be addressed.

00:14:01.900 --> 00:14:05.420
And we've also found that openness is kind of taboo

00:14:05.420 --> 00:14:07.760
in the larger trust and safety community.

00:14:07.760 --> 00:14:10.700
It's been really cool seeing so many trust and safety related

00:14:10.700 --> 00:14:13.450
talks here because that has been kind of pushing back against that

00:14:13.450 --> 00:14:13.820
idea.

00:14:13.820 --> 00:14:17.680
But still within the larger industry people think that if you talk

00:14:17.690 --> 00:14:21.020
about it then it means that bad actors will figure out ways

00:14:21.020 --> 00:14:22.150
to get around your stuff.

00:14:22.150 --> 00:14:24.420
You know it's very security through obscurity which as we

00:14:24.420 --> 00:14:27.100
know from the security world is not really a valid approach.

00:14:27.100 --> 00:14:32.700
And so what we believe is that the missing piece is actual

00:14:32.700 --> 00:14:33.510
tools.

00:14:34.130 --> 00:14:38.420
Things that developers can take and use and build, build on

00:14:38.460 --> 00:14:40.300
and plug into their own platforms.

00:14:41.260 --> 00:14:45.130
And importantly more importantly we believe that these tools must be open

00:14:45.130 --> 00:14:48.130
source so that they're accessible, they're modifiable,

00:14:48.130 --> 00:14:52.220
auditable and part of this trust and safety public commons

00:14:52.220 --> 00:14:52.860
that we're building.

00:14:52.860 --> 00:14:57.660
And as a result Roost is very very open source.

00:14:57.680 --> 00:15:01.830
Everything from not just like technically on a licensing level but also

00:15:01.830 --> 00:15:04.910
the development model and community model that we're building is open

00:15:04.910 --> 00:15:05.600
source.

